## Background (verified this session — do not re-litigate)
A "compiled skill-router" is BUILT and SHIPPED but held INERT behind the default-OFF env flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. When ON, the live advisor attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:371`) to a recommendation the legacy path already computed; it changes ZERO routing decisions (compiled is byte-identical to legacy) and fails safe to a legacy sentinel on any drift (`.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:36-39`). The runtime front door resolves its resolver from a path INSIDE the spec tree (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `.../007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). The eligibility allowlist is duplicated (`advisor-recommend.ts` `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` + `compiled-route.cjs` `HUB_CHILD`). This session added decision packet `012-default-on-decision` (ruling: adopt a phased path to default-on) and alignment PLANS `013-create-skill-alignment` + `014-benchmark-alignment` (both authored, not implemented) under `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/`.

