   168	```
   169	
   170	---
   171	
   172	## 5. PER-FEATURE FILE SCAFFOLD
   173	
   174	Copy this scaffold to create `feature-catalog/{CATEGORY_DIR}/{FEATURE_SLUG}.md`. Both placeholder values must be kebab-case:
   175	
   176	```markdown
   177	---
   178	title: "{FEATURE_NAME}"
   179	description: "{OVERVIEW_ONE_LINE}"
   180	trigger_phrases:
   181	  - "{primary trigger phrase}"
   182	  - "{alternate phrasing}"
   183	  - "{tool or command name}"
   184	  - "{user-visible label if different}"
   185	# importance_tier: "important"   # uncomment only for Tier 1 critical features
   186	version: 1.0.0.0
   187	---
   188	
   189	# {FEATURE_NAME} ({tool_name_or_command})
   190	
   191	<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->
   192	
   193	## 1. OVERVIEW
   194	
   195	{OVERVIEW_ONE_LINE}
   196	
   197	{OVERVIEW_DETAIL}
   198	
   199	---
   200	
   201	## 2. HOW IT WORKS
   202	
   203	<!-- Short section (≤3 paragraphs): write plain prose and delete the sub-headings below.
   204	     Long section (>3 paragraphs): keep or rename sub-headings and delete this comment. -->
   205	
   206	### {PRIMARY_BEHAVIOR_ASPECT}
   207	
   208	{Description of the core behavior from the caller's perspective.}
   209	
   210	### {SECONDARY_BEHAVIOR_ASPECT}
   211	
   212	{Description of a distinct aspect — quality gates, routing logic, async behavior, etc.}
   213	
   214	<!-- Add further H3 sub-headings as needed. Common ones:
   215	     Configuration | Quality Gates | Edge Cases | Async & Safety | Post-Action Behavior -->
   216	
   217	---
   218	
   219	## 3. SOURCE FILES
   220	
   221	### Implementation
   222	
   223	| File | Layer | Role |
   224	|---|---|---|
   225	| `{IMPLEMENTATION_FILE_1}` | {Handler\|Shared\|Script} | {ROLE_1} |
   226	| `{IMPLEMENTATION_FILE_2}` | {Handler\|Shared\|Script} | {ROLE_2} |
   227	
   228	### Validation And Tests
   229	
   230	| File | Type | Role |
   231	|---|---|---|
   232	| `{TEST_FILE_1}` | {Automated test\|Manual playbook} | {TEST_ROLE_1} |
   233	| `{TEST_FILE_2}` | {Automated test\|Manual playbook} | {TEST_ROLE_2} |
   234	
   235	---
   236	
   237	## 4. SOURCE METADATA
   238	
   239	- Group: {CATEGORY_NAME}
   240	- Canonical catalog source: `feature-catalog.md`
   241	- Feature file path: `{CATEGORY_DIR}/{FEATURE_SLUG}.md`
   242	
   243	Related references:
   244	- [{neighboring-feature}.md]({neighboring-feature}.md) — {brief description}
   245	- [{neighboring-feature}.md]({neighboring-feature}.md) — {brief description}
   246	```
   247	
   248	---
   249	
   250	## 6. AUTHORING NOTES
   251	
   252	- Add frontmatter to both the root catalog and per-feature files.
   253	- Add `trigger_phrases` to every per-feature file frontmatter. Phrases must match the H3 feature heading in the root catalog, plus natural-language alternates and the tool or command name.
   254	- Add `importance_tier: "important"` only for Tier 1 critical features that must always surface in search routing. Omit for standard catalog entries.
   255	- In per-feature files, if `HOW IT WORKS` exceeds 3 paragraphs, break it into H3 sub-headings — e.g. `### Core Behavior`, `### Quality Gates`, `### Configuration`, `### Edge Cases`. Long unbroken prose sections should always have navigation anchors.
   256	- Keep the root catalog readable by summarizing behavior instead of dumping raw source-file tables there.
   257	- Put implementation and test anchor detail in the per-feature files.
   258	- Preserve stable file paths once other docs start linking to them.
   259	- Use numbered all-caps H2 section headers in the root catalog. Do not add a Table of Contents.
   260	- Do not write packet-history references such as "added in packet 033" or "Phase 017 update". Rewrite them as current behavior plus a source file, test, or reference-doc link.
   261	
   262	---
   263	
   264	## 7. CHECKLIST
   265	
   266	Before publishing a feature catalog, verify:
   267	
