    47	The harness that produces every run in this tree is the deep-improvement Lane C
    48	skill-benchmark lane. Cross-link both; do not copy them into the hub.
    49	-->
    50	
    51	# {{HUB_NAME}} Skill-Benchmark Artifacts
    52	
    53	> Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `{{HUB_NAME}}` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure. Each run-label folder holds one run's rendered report pair; this file indexes them.
    54	
    55	---
    56	
    57	## 1. OVERVIEW
    58	
    59	The deep-improvement Lane C skill-benchmark harness benchmarks `{{HUB_NAME}}` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This `benchmark/` tree holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes, one run-label folder per run.
    60	
    61	Two trace modes score the same playbook corpus:
    62	
    63	- **router** is deterministic and offline. For a hub skill it replays `hub-router.json` + `mode-registry.json`; for a flat skill it replays the machine-readable router in the skill's `smart-routing.md`. This is the CI gate.
    64	- **live** dispatches each scenario through `cli-opencode` to a real model and grades the model's stated routing plus observed activation. This is the operator default for a true routing verdict.
    65	
    66	The rubric, terminal buckets, and pass thresholds are the deep-improvement Lane C **scoring contract's**, not this index's — see section 6 for the link. Where a number here and the scoring contract disagree, the scoring contract prevails.
    67	
    68	### Key Statistics
    69	
    70	<!-- Fill from the LATEST run-label folder's rendered report. Leave a metric blank
    71	     only if the mode that scores it has not been run; do not invent a value. -->
    72	
    73	| Metric | Value |
    74	|---|---|
    75	| Corpus | {{HUB_NAME}} `manual_testing_playbook` ({{SCENARIO_COUNT}} scenarios across {{CATEGORY_COUNT}} categories) |
    76	| Trace modes | router (deterministic CI gate), live (real dispatch) |
    77	| Latest router verdict | {{VERDICT}}, aggregate {{ROUTER_AGGREGATE}}/100 |
    78	| Latest live verdict | {{VERDICT_OR_NOT_RUN}}, aggregate {{LIVE_AGGREGATE_OR_NA}} |
    79	| D5 connectivity (hard gate) | {{D5_SCORE}}/100 |
    80	
    81	## 2. RUN-LABEL INDEX
    82	
    83	<!-- One row per run-label folder in this tree, newest first. Status ∈ {current,
    84	     superseded, frozen, retired}. Verdict is the rendered report's verdict for
    85	     that run (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), with its aggregate. `baseline/` is the
    86	     frozen comparison anchor — mark it frozen and never regenerate it in place. -->
    87	
    88	| Run label | Date | Trace mode | Verdict | Status | Notes |
    89	|---|---|---|---|---|---|
    90	| `{{RUN_LABEL_1}}` | {{YYYY_MM_DD}} | {{ROUTER_OR_LIVE}} | {{VERDICT}} {{AGGREGATE}} | current | {{WHAT_THIS_RUN_IS}} |
    91	| `{{RUN_LABEL_2}}` | {{YYYY_MM_DD}} | {{ROUTER_OR_LIVE}} | {{VERDICT}} {{AGGREGATE}} | {{STATUS}} | {{WHAT_THIS_RUN_IS}} |
    92	| `baseline` | {{YYYY_MM_DD}} | {{ROUTER_OR_LIVE}} | {{VERDICT}} {{AGGREGATE}} | frozen | Frozen pre-optimization snapshot, the before-comparison anchor, not regenerated |
    93	| `{{ADD_ONE_ROW_PER_FOLDER}}` | {{YYYY_MM_DD}} | {{ROUTER_OR_LIVE}} | {{VERDICT}} {{AGGREGATE}} | {{STATUS}} | {{WHAT_THIS_RUN_IS}} |
    94	
    95	## 3. STRUCTURE
    96	
    97	<!-- Mirror the actual folders on disk. Add new baselines as sibling run-label
    98	     folders rather than overwriting an existing one — a run label is immutable
    99	     once shipped. Delete rows that do not apply to this hub. -->
   100	
   101	```text
   102	benchmark/
   103	+-- {{RUN_LABEL_1}}/    # {{ONE_LINE_PURPOSE}}
   104	+-- {{RUN_LABEL_2}}/    # {{ONE_LINE_PURPOSE}}
   105	`-- baseline/           # Frozen pre-optimization snapshot, do not regenerate
   106	```
   107	
   108	| Path | Purpose |
   109	|---|---|
   110	| `{{RUN_LABEL_1}}/` | {{ONE_LINE_PURPOSE}} |
   111	| `{{RUN_LABEL_2}}/` | {{ONE_LINE_PURPOSE}} |
   112	| `baseline/` | Frozen before-snapshot, the comparison anchor, not reproducible |
   113	
   114	## 4. RE-RUNNING
   115	
   116	Run from the repository root. The runner and its scoring live in the deep-improvement Lane C lane; only the `--skill` and `--outputs-dir` arguments are hub-specific.
   117	
   118	Router mode (deterministic, no network — the CI gate):
   119	
   120	```bash
   121	node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \
   122	  --mode=skill-benchmark --skill={{HUB_PATH}} \
   123	  --outputs-dir={{HUB_PATH}}/benchmark/{{NEW_RUN_LABEL}} \
   124	  --trace-mode=router
   125	```
   126	
   127	Live mode (dispatches through `cli-opencode`, needs a configured provider):
   128	
   129	```bash
   130	SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL={{PROVIDER_MODEL}} SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high \
   131	node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \
   132	  --mode=skill-benchmark --skill={{HUB_PATH}} \
   133	  --outputs-dir={{HUB_PATH}}/benchmark/{{NEW_RUN_LABEL}} \
   134	  --trace-mode=live
   135	```
   136	
   137	Expected result: a `verdict=` line on stdout plus `skill-benchmark-report.json` and `skill-benchmark-report.md` in the outputs dir. The D5 connectivity gate runs first and hard-fails the run on structural breaks — a non-zero exit (`3`) with verdict `BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE` (or `BLOCKED-BY-REGISTRY`), reported inside the same report pair. Add each new run as a fresh sibling run-label folder and a new row in section 2; never overwrite `baseline/`.
   138	
   139	## 5. READING THE REPORTS
   140	
   141	Each run-label folder holds a matched report pair.
   142	
   143	| File | Content |
   144	|---|---|
   145	| `skill-benchmark-report.json` | Machine report: verdict, D1 to D5, funnel, ranked bottlenecks, scenario rows |
   146	| `skill-benchmark-report.md` | The same report rendered for reading, generated from the JSON by `build-report.cjs` to avoid drift |
   147	
   148	Start with the `.md` file for the verdict and the ranked bottlenecks; open the `.json` file for per-scenario detail. The `.md` is an anti-drift **render**, not an authored document: `build-report.cjs` regenerates it from the run JSON, so never hand-edit it — fix the run or the renderer, then re-render.
   149	
   150	## 6. RELATED RESOURCES
   151	
   152	### Related Skills
   153	
   154	| Skill | Relationship | Use When |
   155	|---|---|---|
   156	| [`deep-improvement`]({{PATH_TO_DEEP_IMPROVEMENT_SKILL}}) | Owns the Lane C skill-benchmark harness, runner, and scoring | Running or extending a benchmark |
   157	| [`{{HUB_NAME}}`]({{PATH_TO_HUB_SKILL}}) | The skill under measurement | Reading or tuning the router being scored |
