310- * bullets, and trailing parentheticals like "(when intent is X)". The sibling
311- * `../shared/` form is included so a gold list can credit the family-shared
312- * docs (the operating register, the handoff card) a nested mode loads on
313- * routes, matching what the router actually returns.
314- *
315- * LEGACY / index-table (sk-code) path only. This runs exclusively on the
