.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.7.1.0.md:16:- The four-model GPT-5.5 / GPT-5.6 roster, the `INTENT_SIGNALS` / `RESOURCE_MAP` / `LOADING_LEVELS` router dictionaries, the self-invocation guard, and the ChatGPT OAuth auth pre-flight.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.1.0.md:16:- The four-model GPT-5.5 / GPT-5.6 roster with per-model reasoning-effort ceilings, and the user-override resolution table.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:1:This release expands the documented model roster from a single `gpt-5.5` lock to the full four-model GPT-5.5 / GPT-5.6 set, each with its own reasoning-effort ceiling. All twenty model×effort cells were live-verified callable through cli-codex before the docs were written.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:11:- **Four models documented** -- `gpt-5.5` (default), `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-sol`, replacing the "gpt-5.5 for every task" single-model contract. `gpt-5.5 medium` stays the skill default.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:12:- **Reasoning-effort scale extended** -- added `max` and `ultra` to the documented `none…xhigh` set, with per-model ceilings: `gpt-5.5` ≤ `xhigh`; `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` ≤ `max`; `gpt-5.6-sol` ≤ `ultra`.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:13:- **Selection guidance** -- default `gpt-5.5 medium`; escalate to `gpt-5.6-luna max` for deep implementation and `gpt-5.6-sol xhigh`/`ultra` for verification and review.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:18:- **CX-002 playbook reframed** -- the "gpt-5.5 model lock" scenario now verifies the default pin plus the callable GPT-5.6 roster instead of asserting a single supported model.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:32:Default dispatch is unchanged (`--model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" -c service_tier="fast"`). To reach deeper reasoning, name a GPT-5.6 model per dispatch within its ceiling — e.g. `--model gpt-5.6-sol -c model_reasoning_effort="ultra"`.
