.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:20:- The live executor selects the model from `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL` and always applies its variant setting ([live-executor.cjs:358-379](.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:358-379)), but the report schema currently records only skill ID/root and trace mode ([score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1791-1797](.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1791-1797)). A label such as `live-gpt-5-6-luna-high` is not sufficient provenance unless exact model and variant are persisted in the JSON.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:38:└── live-gpt-5-6-luna-high/
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:47:- `live-gpt-5-6-luna-high/`: model/manual-playbook evidence, advisory to deterministic parity; persist exact `openai/gpt-5.6-luna`, `high`, executor, scenario IDs, and run revision.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:54:4. **P1:** Add exact live executor provenance to report JSON; use `live-gpt-5-6-luna-high` only after the report can prove the routed subject and variant.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:62:  {"id":"F-4-4","area":"archiving","finding":"Lane C live reports currently omit the exact model and variant even though the executor selects them, so a live-gpt-5-6-luna-high folder alone cannot prove the required LUNA HIGH subject.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1791-1797","severity":"P1","actionable":"Persist provider/model, variant, executor, scenario IDs, and run revision in the report JSON or optional per-run README.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:109:1. **Real-model routing verification is a bounded sample, not exhaustive coverage.** A fresh post-flip sweep was re-run (after all 7 serving-authority flips): LUNA/SOL (fast) + MiniMax M3 on 2 authentic playbook prompts per hub × 2 runs, **0 wrong-hub routes** across all 3 models × 7 hubs — SOL and MiniMax passed 2/2 on every hub; the LUNA non-passes are transport timeouts, not misroutes. Fresh verdicts are in `real-model/<hub>/verdict.json`. This confirms the pre-flip P4a T9 result held post-cutover, consistent with the recompiles being route-gold byte-identical. It remains a 2-prompts-per-hub sample, not the full playbook corpus.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:1:# Iteration 5 — gpt-5.6-sol high — focus: activation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:1:# Iteration 3 — gpt-5.6-sol high — focus: playbooks
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:14:Each of the seven hub roots should then gain one thinner `compiled-routing/luna-high-route-follow.md` scenario. Reuse a shipped playbook prompt, execute flag-off and flag-on probes, and assert identical top-level skill/mode plus the expected compiled target. This belongs at the hub root because those playbooks already validate live advisor-plus-mode behavior—for example `sk-code` has a dedicated advisor category (`sk-code/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:220-226`), `sk-design` explicitly captures the advisor vote and resolved mode (`sk-design/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:47-53`), and `system-deep-loop` does the same (`system-deep-loop/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:39-44`). Author each new file through the `create-manual-testing-playbook` template: one canonical per-feature file carrying exact prompt, command, signals, evidence, verdict, and triage (`sk-doc/create-manual-testing-playbook/SKILL.md:207-231`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:18:First, the prompt-time advisor hook currently cannot transport the compiled decision. The native response schema accepts `compiledRoute` (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/schemas/advisor-tool-schemas.ts:208-222`) and the native handler attaches it (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:362-371`), but the hook subprocess recommendation type has no such field (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/lib/subprocess.ts:16-23`) and its rendered brief only tells the model to use the top skill (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/lib/render.ts:197-200`). A LUNA run through the current hook can therefore pass while never observing the compiled mode decision. Add compiled action/targets/status to the hook contract and a hook-level assertion before accepting real-model evidence.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:28:`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=<0|1> codex exec --model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="high" -c service_tier="fast" -c approval_policy=never --sandbox read-only -o <stdout-evidence> "<route-only prompt>" 2> <stderr-evidence>`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:30:The model and effort are valid (`cli-codex/SKILL.md:235-242`), and the CLI contract requires explicit model, effort, and service tier (`cli-codex/SKILL.md:267-268`). Keep routing validation read-only and tell LUNA to return the injected advisor skill, compiled action, target mode/packet, and serving status without executing the underlying user task. Treat timeout as `SKIP` with an infrastructure blocker, not routing failure: earlier LUNA routing runs hit the existing 150-second ceiling repeatedly (`010-live-activation/real-model/run-log.txt:50-57`, `:95-102`, `:143-150`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:34:1. P0 — carry `compiledRoute` and serving status through the prompt-time hook; otherwise LUNA never sees the decision being tested.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:38:5. P1 — add one flag-off/flag-on LUNA-high route-follow scenario to each eligible hub root; do not duplicate them in child playbooks.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:46:  {"id":"F-3-3","area":"unnamed","finding":"The prompt-time hook cannot machine-enforce compiled routing because its recommendation type and rendered brief discard compiledRoute.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/lib/subprocess.ts:16","severity":"P0","actionable":"Carry compiled action, targets, and serving status through the hook subprocess contract and render them into the injected advisor brief before running LUNA scenarios.","novelty":"new"},
